              </a:rPr>
              <a:t>Purpose: ingest Excel/CSV files as structured documents (not raw CSV text).
_detect_header_row(rows) — scores first 8 rows for header-likeness using: unique values, alphabetic cells, cell length ≥ 3. Handles files with metadata rows before the header.
_normalize_headers() — deduplicates column names ('Amount' → 'Amount 2'), fills blank headers with 'Column A', 'Column B', etc.
Each row becomes a Document with row_number, column=value pairs, and sheet_name in metadata.
Empty rows skipped. Multi-sheet workbooks produce separate document sets per sheet.</a:t>
            </a:r>
            <a:endParaRPr lang="en-US" sz="1000" dirty="0"/>
