              </a:rPr>
              <a:t>Plain CSV ingestion loses structure: 'Region,Spend,Reserve' becomes meaningless fragments.
Workbook loader produces semantically rich chunks:
'Region: APAC | Annual Spend USD: 1200000 | Risk Score: 8'
These chunks match data_analyst queries like 'highest spend region' because the field names are embedded in the text.
Header detection prevents misclassifying metadata rows (e.g. 'Report: Q3 2024') as data.
Works with .csv, .xlsx, .xls files. Detects file type from extension.</a:t>
